    "subtitle": "A Formal System for Specifying Complex Artifacts",
    "abstract": "STRATUM v2.5.0-alpha introduces conformance levels (K0-K3) and adds the seventh guarantee G7 (Explainability). This ALPHA release defines the Kernel (K0) as a 2-hour reading path covering core data structures, well-formedness, six guarantees (G1-G6), and basic operations. K1 (Certified-Aware) adds G7 with irreducible unsat cores and the Policy System for automated remediation. Building on v2.4.4, this version includes: (1) schema evolution with compatibility rules (§16), (2) STPA/FMEA hazard integration (§27), (3) formal attenuation properties (§28), (4) cross-standard DO-178C ↔ ISO 26262 traceability (§29), (5) LSL-style tier boundary semantics (§30), and (6) comprehensive 100+ term glossary (§30). The specification maintains backward compatibility while enabling regulated industry adoption through explicit conformance tiers.",
